The stripURLFromError function as implemented does not actually remove the webhook URL from the error's string representation if the underlying error is a *url.Error. Since fmt.Errorf with %w preserves the original error, calling .Error() on the result will still include the URL. This could lead to sensitive webhook tokens being leaked into application logs. Consider explicitly checking for *url.Error and redacting its URL field or returning only its inner error.

```go
func stripURLFromError(err error) error {
	if err == nil {
		return nil
	}
	var urlErr *url.Error
	if errors.As(err, &urlErr) {
		return fmt.Errorf("delivery error (webhook URL redacted): %s [redacted]: %w", urlErr.Op, urlErr.Err)
	}
	return fmt.Errorf("delivery error (webhook URL redacted): %w", err)
}
```

