The doAttempt function should check if the parent context is already cancelled before starting a new HTTP request. Deriving a timeout context from an already cancelled parent context will cause doPost to fail immediately, but it is more efficient to return the context error directly and stop the retry loop.

```go
func doAttempt(ctx context.Context, client *http.Client, cfg postConfig, body []byte) (done bool, retryWait time.Duration, err error) {
	if err := ctx.Err(); err != nil {
		return true, 0, err
	}
```
